servings: 2
cuisine: North America
time required: 40 minutes
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into 1-inch-thick pieces. Halve,
peel, and cut @red onion{1} into ½-inch-thick wedges; mince a few wedges until you
have 1 TBSP (2 TBSP for 4 servings).

Toss carrots and onion wedges on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of
@cooking oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{25-30%minutes}.

While veggies roast, dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Place in a
#medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil
and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

> For a smoother texture, peel potatoes first.

Reserve ½ cup potato cooking liquid, then drain and return potatoes to pot. Keep
covered off heat until ready to mash.

While potatoes cook, pat @organic chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with
#paper towels{}. Season all over with salt and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and
cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

> Swap in chicken or organic chicken for pork; cook until browned and cooked
> through, 3-5 minutes per side.

Turn off heat; transfer chicken to a #cutting board{}. Wipe out pan.

Meanwhile, strip @rosemary{¼%ounce} leaves from stems; finely chop leaves until
you have 2 tsp (3 tsp for 4 servings).

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for chicken over medium heat. Add minced
onion and chopped rosemary. Cook, stirring often, until onion is softened,
~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @chicken demi-glace{1} and ¼ cup water (1⁄3 cup for 4 servings). Bring to a
simmer and cook until slightly thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Turn off heat and stir in 1 TBSP @butter{2%tablespoon}(divided) until melted.

Return pot with drained potatoes to medium-low heat. Add @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon}
and 1 TBSP butter (2 TBSP for 4 servings). Mash with a #potato masher{} until
smooth, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed. Season
generously with salt and pepper.

Slice chicken crosswise.

> Thinly slice chicken or organic chicken crosswise.

Divide chicken, mashed potatoes, and veggies between plates. Top chicken with
sauce and serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.